   <b>OBJECTIVE</b>

   </br>Nevo is looking for seasoned software development professionals.  You should have worked on several large development projects in a variety of applications and industries.  You should have extensive experience in developing the overall design for implementing a client software solution, having participated actively with the client during requirements discovery, worked with the team to evaluate candidate technologies and approaches, and guided software developers as they implement the solution. Nevo expects a Seasoned Systems Architect/Developer to have broad "generalist" experience in a wide variety of applications, platforms, languages, databases, and development tools.

   <p>
   <b>MAJOR DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</b>

   <ul class="listText">
   		<li>Work closely with clients to understand the detailed technical and business requirements associated with a project
   		</li><li>Develop system and software designs that achieve the client’s technical goals   within the clients technical, schedule, budgetary, and other constraints and win broad support for the chosen design
   		</li><li>Lead team efforts to select and define the tools, approaches, and standards to be used in developing each system
   		</li><li>Not only be a technical lead, but also participate in the development of various software components as an individual contributor.
   		</li><li>Demonstrate the professional and technical standards Nevo expects and ensure Nevo’s performance and deliverables meet them
   		</li><li>Communicate effectively to all parties and establish effective relationship with client’s leading technical staff
   		</li><li>Advance Nevo’s reputation for developing superior technical solutions to client needs
   		</li>

   </ul>

   <b>ESSENTIAL QUALIFICATIONS</b>

   <ul class="listText">
   		<li>BS or BA in a computer science or equivalent technical experience
		</li><li>Demonstrated accomplishments designing and implementing several complex software systems in multiple environments (Solaris, NT/Win2K/Win3K, HP, Pyramid, IBM RISC/6000, IBM 370s) using variety of languages (Java, JSP, ASP.NET, C#, ASP, Perl, PL/SQL, SQL, C, Korne Shell, Perl)
		</li><li>Experienced developing distributed software applications in J2EE (EJB, Java Servlet, JSP, JDBC, JNDI, JMS and XML), Microsoft .NET
		</li><li>Experience with Internet application servers (Tomcat, IBM WebSphere, SunOne Enterprise Server, BEA WebLogic, Oracle Application Server; ATG Dynamo, JRun, IIS)
		</li><li>Extensive experience with RDBMS databases (Oracle, MS SQL Server, MS Access, UDB DB2, Sybase)
		</li><li>Strong understanding of software development methodologies, especially agile software development approaches
		</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills with an appreciation for and ability to communicate with and respond to the needs of diverse audiences
		</li><li>Excellent writing skills; the ability to write clear, concise, comprehensive documents tailored to both technical and business audiences
		</li><li>Comfortable in a multi-task, deadline-oriented environment.
		</li>
   </ul>

   <b>ADDITIONAL CONSIDERATIONS</b>

   <ul class="listText">
		<li>Professional services or consulting work experience
		</li><li>Comfortable speaking to groups in both formal and informal settings
		</li>
   </ul>

